The paper deals with the problem of computing replacement paths in a graph, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. The problem involves finding shortest paths in a modified graph obtained by removing edges or vertices from a given shortest path. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including data structures, discrete mathematics, computational geometry, artificial intelligence, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
